### 2c. PaymentReminderTask (`payment_reminder_task.go`)
Inject `billingService.InvoiceService` and `notificationService.NotificationService`. Call `invoiceService.ListOverdue(ctx)` to get overdue invoices, then for each, send a notification. If `ListOverdue` doesn't exist, create a simpler version: log the intent and return nil (the invoice service can be extended later).

### 2d. PaymentRetryTask (`payment_retry_task.go`)
Inject `billingService.PaymentService`. Call `paymentService.ListFailedPayments(ctx)` to get failed payments where `retry_count < max_retries`, then for each call `paymentService.RetryPayment(ctx, paymentID)`. If `ListFailedPayments` doesn't exist on the service interface, check the payment repository for a `ListFailed` method and use it. If neither exists, log and return nil.

### 2e. PolicyLapseTask (`policy_lapse_task.go`)
Inject `policyService.PolicyService`. Check if `LapseOverduePolicies(ctx)` or similar method exists. If it does, call it. If not, log "Policy lapse task: service method not yet available" and return nil. Do NOT create new service methods — just wire what exists.

### 2f. PreAuthExpiryTask (`preauth_expiry_task.go`)
Inject `preauthService.PreAuthService`. Check if `ExpireOldPreAuths(ctx)` or similar exists. If it does, call it. If not, log and return nil.

### 2g. ReconciliationTask (`reconciliation_task.go`)
Inject `billingService.PaymentService`. Check if a reconciliation method exists. If not, log and return nil.

### 2h. NotificationRetryTask (`notification_retry_task.go`)
Inject `notificationService.NotificationService`. Call `RetryFailed(ctx)` if it exists. Check the notification service interface first.

